sections.body:
There are no arbiters, no dispute states, no contestation windows. Money moves only by mechanical rules:
– delivery certified by the receiving hub: the carrier collects the leg's gross directly from the sender and their bond is released;
– no pickup within 24 hours of funding: the carrier's bond is collected by the sender, the payment is cancelled and the parcel returns to the board;
– no delivery within 48 hours of pickup: the carrier's bond is collected by the sender and the shipment closes as lost;
– return to the leg's departure hub: payment and bond cancelled, no payout; the ceding hub is bound to take back what it certified at checkout;
– storage expired: the parcel is released to the hub under §10.

Consequences accepted by every party: in unprovable cases — damage that no mechanical rule attributes to anyone — nobody is compensated; the loss stays with the sender and reputation records the behaviour (§11). There is no transport insurance of any kind: the custody bond, sized by the sender, is the only peer-to-peer guarantee. Hub fees already paid at handoffs stay paid: they compensate a service already rendered.

The minimization principle (art. 5(1)(c) GDPR) is implemented in the software, not merely declared:
– no geotags: photos are re-encoded on your device before the fingerprint is computed — EXIF metadata (GPS position, device details) never leave the phone; as an extra defence the server rejects uploads containing GPS coordinates;
– no GPS tracking of carriers: only the trip's declared origin and destination are recorded, never the real-time position;
– no faces required: the photos in the flow picture the parcel and are visible only to the shipment's participants, never to the public;
– custody chain without personal data: events record facts and fingerprints (hashes), never emails or other personal data;
– credentials never in cleartext in the database: pickup codes and personal codes are stored as hashes only; the QR on the parcel carries an opaque identifier that authorizes nothing on its own;
– technical cookies only: session (httpOnly) and language; no profiling or third-party cookies;
– URLs in emails carry only the shipment identifier: codes stay in the message body.
